Implementation plans for this project live in docs/plans/. When I give you a plan:
- Follow it exactly. Do not add features, files, or abstractions it doesn't specify.
- Treat the "Guardrails for Cursor (DO NOT)" section as hard constraints.
- Keep middleware.ts edge-safe (no @/lib/* imports).
- When you're done, report the exact files you changed and confirm build/typecheck passes.
If something in the plan seems wrong, or a build error contradicts it, stop and tell me
the exact error — do not improvise a workaround.

Never edit CLAUDE.md or docs/project-context.md. Those are maintained elsewhere — leave them alone.

After any architecturally significant change — a Prisma/schema change, a new or changed
business rule, a new env var, or a new convention — append ONE dated line to
docs/CHANGELOG.md under the "## Pending reconcile" heading (create the file and heading
if missing):
- YYYY-MM-DD [schema|rule|env|convention] what changed and why, in one line
Do NOT append for cosmetic changes or bug fixes. One line only — never prose,
never edit existing entries, never touch any other doc.